@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Sequence - mysql/MySqlDbSystem
hide footbox
skinparam sequence {
  actorBorderColor #0f172a
  actorBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  participantBorderColor #0f172a
  participantBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  participantFontColor #0f172a
  lifeLineBorderColor #94a3b8
  groupBorderColor #cbd5e1
  groupBackgroundColor #f8fafc
}
actor Kubernetes
participant Controller
participant BaseReconciler
participant "LegacyAdapter" as ServiceManager
participant OCI
participant "Kubernetes Secret" as SecretStore
note over BaseReconciler,ServiceManager
shared resolution:
shared/diagrams/shared-resolution-sequence.svg
shared delete:
shared/diagrams/shared-delete-sequence.svg
end note
Kubernetes -> Controller: enqueue MySqlDbSystem reconcile
Controller -> BaseReconciler: Reconcile(request)
BaseReconciler -> ServiceManager: reconcile desired MySqlDbSystem
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetDbSystem
opt list lookup fallback
ServiceManager -> OCI: ListDbSystems(filters:\ncompartment_id, configuration_id,\ndatabase_management, db_system_id\n(+4 more))
OCI --> ServiceManager: matching collection items
end
alt create or bind path
ServiceManager -> OCI: CreateDbSystem
loop create pending CREATING, UPDATING
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetDbSystem
end
else update or drift path
ServiceManager -> OCI: UpdateDbSystem
loop update pending UPDATING
ServiceManager -> OCI: GetDbSystem
end
end
opt repo-authored secret side effects
ServiceManager -> SecretStore: read required input secret and write\nready-only connection secret
end
opt delete requested
note right of ServiceManager
delete remains repo-authored unsupported
despite DeleteDbSystem
end note
end
ServiceManager --> BaseReconciler: status=manual, finalizer=none
BaseReconciler --> Controller: requeue on provisioning, updating
note right of ServiceManager
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-resolution-sequence.svg
shared delete diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-delete-sequence.svg
Start from the shared resolution sequence for
OCID binding, datasource pagination, and
create-or-update dispatch.
Layer the shared delete sequence when finalizer
retention, delete confirmation, work-request
polling, or Secret cleanup apply.
archetype batch: Legacy-adapter controllers
follow the shared resolution and delete
sequences but preserve handwritten stop
conditions until promotion is safe.
service: mysql
slug: mysqldbsystem
kind: MySqlDbSystem
archetype: legacy-adapter
status/finalizer: manual / none
requeue: provisioning, updating
provider states: create CREATING, UPDATING;
update UPDATING; delete DELETING
mutable/forceNew: access_mode,
backup_policy.copy_policies.backup_copy_retention_in_days,
backup_policy.copy_policies.copy_to_region,
backup_policy.defined_tags (+50 more) /
admin_password, admin_username,
availability_domain, compartment_id (+12 more)
open gaps: bind-versus-create,
delete-confirmation, endpoint-materialization,
legacy-adapter, list-lookup (+3 more)
Create reads username and password secrets
before submitting the OCI request.
Endpoint secret materialization only happens
after the DB system reaches ACTIVE.
Delete remains an unsupported legacy path, so no
confirmed terminating phase exists today.
end note
@enduml
